race.comment: VORACIOUS (5) grows a leg for hoop Jones who has two wins and two placings from just five steers and will be high on confidence following a last-start victory over this track and trip. Should be going very close again. The well-related LARRIKIN ROGUE (7) (half to G3 winner Shamalia) goes well around this circuit with a win and five placings from eight spins. Better than recent efforts suggest and can improve sharply without surprising. CHIEF WITNESS (9) has been thereabouts in all four runs this preparation and maps well for this from gate two. Include in calculations. KODIAK (3) best of the rest.
